Encapsulation
1. Wrapping up the implementation of data members and methods in class.
2. Encapsulation uses access modifiers and getter & setter methods to implement.
3. Encapsulation is the process of CONTAINING the Information.
4. It is based on the Implementation Level and Internal working


Abstraction
1. Hiding unnecessary details and showing only the valuable information.
2. It uses abstract classes and interfaces to implement.
3. Abstraction is the process of GAINING the Information.
4. It is based on the Design Level and External Outlook


https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/difference-between-abstraction-and-encapsulation-in-java-with-examples/#:~:text=Abstraction%20vs%20Encapsulation,from%20outside%20world.